description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a registered nurse that enjoys a challenge?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you want to develop your knowledge in the field of Continuing Healthcare?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If so, CCG (Health Assessment and Review Team - CHC) want to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an exciting opportunity that will ensure that your skills and experience are fully utilized in the determination of eligibility of clients for NHS Continuing Healthcare and Funded Nursing Care in the BNSSG area. The role will involve working with clients and professionals from other disciplines/ services and as such the ability to communicate clearly and concisely is essential. The job holder may be involved with clients in other areas of care, such as learning difficulties or mental health. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The CHC (Health Assessment and Review Team) is based at South Plaza, though as the post holder you will be expected to travel and may spend some part of your time working from home. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The CCG is a friendly group of staff; please give us a ring to find out more. You are welcome to come for an informal visit via Microsoft team chat&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact: Clara Biu or Donna Witchard on Tel:0117 3300201&lt;/p&gt;
